# Markdown Writing Standards

Apply these conventions when creating or editing any Markdown documentation.

## Document structure

- One H1 per document as the main title
- Follow logical heading progression: H1 → H2 → H3 — never skip levels
- Include a blank line before and after every heading
- Include a blank line before and after every list or code block
- For documents longer than 3 sections, add a table of contents with relative links

## Headings

Use ATX style (`#` symbols) not underline style. Title case for headings. Single space between `#` and text.

```markdown
## Good Heading

Content starts here after blank line.
```

## Lists

Use `-` for unordered lists consistently. Use 2-space indentation for nested items. Keep list items parallel in structure and concise.

## Code blocks

Always specify a language for fenced code blocks:

```markdown
```bash
terraform init
```
```

Use backticks for inline code, commands, file paths, and technical terms: `terraform init`, `main.tf`, `var.environment`.

## Links

Use descriptive link text — never "click here" or raw URLs:

```markdown
See [Terraform provider documentation](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/hashicorp/azurerm/latest/docs).
```

Use relative paths for repository-internal links.

## Tables

Align column separators for readability. Include a header row. Keep cell content concise.

## Quality rules

- Verify all code examples are functional before committing
- Check all internal links are valid relative paths
- Line length should not exceed 120 characters
- No trailing whitespace
